We choose K = 5 because it represents the perfect mathematical sweet spot on both metrics:
* Highest Silhouette Score (Red Line): The red curve peaks exactly at K = 5 (at around 0.75), proving that 5 clusters give us the cleanest separation and the most cohesive groups.
* Inertia Flattening (Blue Line): At K = 5, the blue curve flattens out significantly, showing that adding more than 5 clusters does not add any real value to our model.

